<body>
<h1> Syntax </h1>
<br>
alias                  : lists your aliases<br>
alias [abbrev] [subst] : create a new alias<br>
alias [abbrev]         : deletes the alias<br>
<br>
<h1> Description </h1>
<br>
This command allows you to replace a commonly used phrase by a shortened<br>
version.  Anywhere you type the abbreviation it replaces it with the<br>
substitution.  If the first letter of the abbreviation is a * then the<br>
alias only takes affect if the first word on the line.  <br>
<br>
EXAMPLES:<br>
<br>
alias df drink fountain  : to drink from a fountain, type df.<br>
alias df                 : deletes df alias.<br>
<br>
Preceding an alias with an * makes the alias only take effect if it is<br>
the first thing typed on a line.<br>
<br>
EXAMPLES<br>
<br>
alias *ef eat food : to eat food, type ef, and it will only occur if<br>
typed at the beginning of the line.<br>
</html>
</body>
